{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":988,"text":"Let me tell you a story."},{"time":3304,"text":"It goes back 200 million years."},{"time":5103,"text":"It's a story of the neocortex,"},{"time":7087,"text":"which means \"new rind.\""},{"time":9061,"text":"So in these early mammals,"},{"time":11492,"text":"because only mammals have a neocortex,"},{"time":13547,"text":"rodent-like creatures."},{"time":15211,"text":"It was the size of a postage stamp and just as thin,"},{"time":18790,"text":"and was a thin covering around"},{"time":20229,"text":"their walnut-sized brain,"},{"time":22493,"text":"but it was capable of a new type of thinking."},{"time":26194,"text":"Rather than the fixed behaviors"},{"time":27761,"text":"that non-mammalian animals have,"},{"time":29753,"text":"it could invent new behaviors."},{"time":32445,"text":"So a mouse is escaping a predator,"},{"time":34998,"text":"its path is blocked,"},{"time":36538,"text":"it'll try to invent a new solution."},{"time":38667,"text":"That may work, it may not,"},{"time":39933,"text":"but if it does, it will remember that"},{"time":41843,"text":"and have a new behavior,"},{"time":43135,"text":"and that can actually spread virally"},{"time":44592,"text":"through the rest of the community."},{"time":46787,"text":"Another mouse watching this could say,"},{"time":48396,"text":"\"Hey, that was pretty clever, going around that rock,\""},{"time":51100,"text":"and it could adopt a new behavior as well."}]},{"cues":[{"time":54825,"text":"Non-mammalian animals"},{"time":56542,"text":"couldn't do any of those things."},{"time":58255,"text":"They had fixed behaviors."},{"time":59470,"text":"Now they could learn a new behavior"},{"time":60801,"text":"but not in the course of one lifetime."},{"time":63377,"text":"In the course of maybe a thousand lifetimes,"},{"time":65144,"text":"it could evolve a new fixed behavior."},{"time":68474,"text":"That was perfectly okay 200 million years ago."},{"time":71851,"text":"The environment changed very slowly."},{"time":73832,"text":"It could take 10,000 years for there to be"},{"time":75386,"text":"a significant environmental change,"},{"time":77478,"text":"and during that period of time"},{"time":78860,"text":"it would evolve a new behavior."}]},{"cues":[{"time":81789,"text":"Now that went along fine,"},{"time":83310,"text":"but then something happened."},{"time":85014,"text":"Sixty-five million years ago,"},{"time":87260,"text":"there was a sudden, violent\nchange to the environment."},{"time":89875,"text":"We call it the Cretaceous extinction event."},{"time":93380,"text":"That's when the dinosaurs went extinct,"},{"time":95673,"text":"that's when 75 percent of the"},{"time":99122,"text":"animal and plant species went extinct,"},{"time":101868,"text":"and that's when mammals"},{"time":103613,"text":"overtook their ecological niche,"},{"time":105765,"text":"and to anthropomorphize, biological evolution said,"},{"time":109419,"text":"\"Hmm, this neocortex is pretty good stuff,\""},{"time":111444,"text":"and it began to grow it."},{"time":113237,"text":"And mammals got bigger,"},{"time":114579,"text":"their brains got bigger at an even faster pace,"},{"time":117494,"text":"and the neocortex got bigger even faster than that"},{"time":121301,"text":"and developed these distinctive ridges and folds"},{"time":124230,"text":"basically to increase its surface area."},{"time":127111,"text":"If you took the human neocortex"},{"time":128930,"text":"and stretched it out,"},{"time":130231,"text":"it's about the size of a table napkin,"},{"time":131944,"text":"and it's still a thin structure."},{"time":133250,"text":"It's about the thickness of a table napkin."},{"time":135230,"text":"But it has so many convolutions and ridges"},{"time":137727,"text":"it's now 80 percent of our brain,"},{"time":140802,"text":"and that's where we do our thinking,"},{"time":143263,"text":"and it's the great sublimator."},{"time":145024,"text":"We still have that old brain"},{"time":146138,"text":"that provides our basic drives and motivations,"},{"time":148902,"text":"but I may have a drive for conquest,"},{"time":151618,"text":"and that'll be sublimated by the neocortex"},{"time":154333,"text":"into writing a poem or inventing an app"},{"time":157242,"text":"or giving a TED Talk,"},{"time":158751,"text":"and it's really the neocortex that's where"},{"time":162373,"text":"the action is."}]},{"cues":[{"time":164341,"text":"Fifty years ago, I wrote a paper"},{"time":166058,"text":"describing how I thought the brain worked,"},{"time":167976,"text":"and I described it as a series of modules."},{"time":171175,"text":"Each module could do things with a pattern."},{"time":173303,"text":"It could learn a pattern. It could remember a pattern."},{"time":176049,"text":"It could implement a pattern."},{"time":177456,"text":"And these modules were organized in hierarchies,"},{"time":180135,"text":"and we created that hierarchy with our own thinking."},{"time":183089,"text":"And there was actually very little to go on"},{"time":186422,"text":"50 years ago."},{"time":187984,"text":"It led me to meet President Johnson."},{"time":190099,"text":"I've been thinking about this for 50 years,"},{"time":192272,"text":"and a year and a half ago I came out with the book"},{"time":195100,"text":"\"How To Create A Mind,\""},{"time":196365,"text":"which has the same thesis,"},{"time":197978,"text":"but now there's a plethora of evidence."},{"time":200790,"text":"The amount of data we're getting about the brain"},{"time":202604,"text":"from neuroscience is doubling every year."},{"time":204807,"text":"Spatial resolution of brainscanning of all types"},{"time":207461,"text":"is doubling every year."},{"time":209746,"text":"We can now see inside a living brain"},{"time":211463,"text":"and see individual interneural connections"},{"time":214333,"text":"connecting in real time, firing in real time."},{"time":217036,"text":"We can see your brain create your thoughts."},{"time":219455,"text":"We can see your thoughts create your brain,"},{"time":221030,"text":"which is really key to how it works."}]},{"cues":[{"time":223029,"text":"So let me describe briefly how it works."},{"time":225248,"text":"I've actually counted these modules."},{"time":227523,"text":"We have about 300 million of them,"},{"time":229569,"text":"and we create them in these hierarchies."},{"time":231798,"text":"I'll give you a simple example."},{"time":233880,"text":"I've got a bunch of modules"},{"time":236685,"text":"that can recognize the crossbar to a capital A,"},{"time":240088,"text":"and that's all they care about."},{"time":242002,"text":"A beautiful song can play,"},{"time":243580,"text":"a pretty girl could walk by,"},{"time":245014,"text":"they don't care, but they see\na crossbar to a capital A,"},{"time":247860,"text":"they get very excited and they say \"crossbar,\""},{"time":250881,"text":"and they put out a high probability"},{"time":252993,"text":"on their output axon."},{"time":254627,"text":"That goes to the next level,"},{"time":255960,"text":"and these layers are organized in conceptual levels."},{"time":258710,"text":"Each is more abstract than the next one,"},{"time":260566,"text":"so the next one might say \"capital A.\""},{"time":262984,"text":"That goes up to a higher\nlevel that might say \"Apple.\""},{"time":265875,"text":"Information flows down also."},{"time":268042,"text":"If the apple recognizer has seen A-P-P-L,"},{"time":270978,"text":"it'll think to itself, \"Hmm, I\nthink an E is probably likely,\""},{"time":274197,"text":"and it'll send a signal down to all the E recognizers"},{"time":276761,"text":"saying, \"Be on the lookout for an E,"},{"time":278380,"text":"I think one might be coming.\""},{"time":279936,"text":"The E recognizers will lower their threshold"},{"time":282779,"text":"and they see some sloppy\nthing, could be an E."},{"time":284724,"text":"Ordinarily you wouldn't think so,"},{"time":286214,"text":"but we're expecting an E, it's good enough,"},{"time":288223,"text":"and yeah, I've seen an E, and then apple says,"},{"time":290040,"text":"\"Yeah, I've seen an Apple.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":291768,"text":"Go up another five levels,"},{"time":293514,"text":"and you're now at a pretty high level"},{"time":294867,"text":"of this hierarchy,"},{"time":296436,"text":"and stretch down into the different senses,"},{"time":298789,"text":"and you may have a module\nthat sees a certain fabric,"},{"time":301444,"text":"hears a certain voice quality,\nsmells a certain perfume,"},{"time":304288,"text":"and will say, \"My wife has entered the room.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":306801,"text":"Go up another 10 levels, and now you're at"},{"time":308696,"text":"a very high level."},{"time":309856,"text":"You're probably in the frontal cortex,"},{"time":311793,"text":"and you'll have modules that say, \"That was ironic."},{"time":315560,"text":"That's funny. She's pretty.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":317930,"text":"You might think that those are more sophisticated,"},{"time":320035,"text":"but actually what's more complicated"},{"time":321541,"text":"is the hierarchy beneath them."},{"time":324210,"text":"There was a 16-year-old girl, she had brain surgery,"},{"time":326830,"text":"and she was conscious because the surgeons"},{"time":328881,"text":"wanted to talk to her."},{"time":330418,"text":"You can do that because there's no pain receptors"},{"time":332240,"text":"in the brain."},{"time":333278,"text":"And whenever they stimulated particular,"},{"time":335078,"text":"very small points on her neocortex,"},{"time":337541,"text":"shown here in red, she would laugh."},{"time":340206,"text":"So at first they thought they were triggering"},{"time":341646,"text":"some kind of laugh reflex,"},{"time":343366,"text":"but no, they quickly realized they had found"},{"time":345885,"text":"the points in her neocortex that detect humor,"},{"time":348929,"text":"and she just found everything hilarious"},{"time":350898,"text":"whenever they stimulated these points."},{"time":353335,"text":"\"You guys are so funny just standing around,\""},{"time":355260,"text":"was the typical comment,"},{"time":356998,"text":"and they weren't funny,"},{"time":359300,"text":"not while doing surgery."}]},{"cues":[{"time":362547,"text":"So how are we doing today?"},{"time":367377,"text":"Well, computers are actually beginning to master"},{"time":370431,"text":"human language with techniques"},{"time":372432,"text":"that are similar to the neocortex."},{"time":375299,"text":"I actually described the algorithm,"},{"time":376813,"text":"which is similar to something called"},{"time":378867,"text":"a hierarchical hidden Markov model,"},{"time":381100,"text":"something I've worked on since the '90s."},{"time":384341,"text":"\"Jeopardy\" is a very broad natural language game,"},{"time":387579,"text":"and Watson got a higher score"},{"time":389471,"text":"than the best two players combined."},{"time":391471,"text":"It got this query correct:"},{"time":393970,"text":"\"A long, tiresome speech"},{"time":396055,"text":"delivered by a frothy pie topping,\""},{"time":398207,"text":"and it quickly responded,\n\"What is a meringue harangue?\""},{"time":401003,"text":"And Jennings and the other guy didn't get that."},{"time":403638,"text":"It's a pretty sophisticated example of"},{"time":405564,"text":"computers actually understanding human language,"},{"time":407478,"text":"and it actually got its knowledge by reading"},{"time":409130,"text":"Wikipedia and several other encyclopedias."}]},{"cues":[{"time":412915,"text":"Five to 10 years from now,"},{"time":415048,"text":"search engines will actually be based on"},{"time":417232,"text":"not just looking for combinations of words and links"},{"time":420026,"text":"but actually understanding,"},{"time":421940,"text":"reading for understanding the billions of pages"},{"time":424351,"text":"on the web and in books."},{"time":427084,"text":"So you'll be walking along, and Google will pop up"},{"time":429700,"text":"and say, \"You know, Mary, you expressed concern"},{"time":432781,"text":"to me a month ago that your glutathione supplement"},{"time":435800,"text":"wasn't getting past the blood-brain barrier."},{"time":438031,"text":"Well, new research just came out 13 seconds ago"},{"time":440624,"text":"that shows a whole new approach to that"},{"time":442335,"text":"and a new way to take glutathione."},{"time":444328,"text":"Let me summarize it for you.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":446890,"text":"Twenty years from now, we'll have nanobots,"},{"time":450574,"text":"because another exponential trend"},{"time":452201,"text":"is the shrinking of technology."},{"time":453816,"text":"They'll go into our brain"},{"time":456186,"text":"through the capillaries"},{"time":457889,"text":"and basically connect our neocortex"},{"time":460366,"text":"to a synthetic neocortex in the cloud"},{"time":463551,"text":"providing an extension of our neocortex."},{"time":467142,"text":"Now today, I mean,"},{"time":468720,"text":"you have a computer in your phone,"},{"time":470250,"text":"but if you need 10,000 computers for a few seconds"},{"time":473004,"text":"to do a complex search,"},{"time":474499,"text":"you can access that for a second or two in the cloud."},{"time":477895,"text":"In the 2030s, if you need some extra neocortex,"},{"time":480990,"text":"you'll be able to connect to that in the cloud"},{"time":483263,"text":"directly from your brain."},{"time":484911,"text":"So I'm walking along and I say,"},{"time":486454,"text":"\"Oh, there's Chris Anderson."},{"time":487817,"text":"He's coming my way."},{"time":489342,"text":"I'd better think of something clever to say."},{"time":491677,"text":"I've got three seconds."},{"time":493201,"text":"My 300 million modules in my neocortex"},{"time":496298,"text":"isn't going to cut it."},{"time":497538,"text":"I need a billion more.\""},{"time":498784,"text":"I'll be able to access that in the cloud."},{"time":502107,"text":"And our thinking, then, will be a hybrid"},{"time":504919,"text":"of biological and non-biological thinking,"},{"time":508441,"text":"but the non-biological portion"},{"time":510339,"text":"is subject to my law of accelerating returns."},{"time":513021,"text":"It will grow exponentially."},{"time":515260,"text":"And remember what happens"},{"time":517276,"text":"the last time we expanded our neocortex?"},{"time":519921,"text":"That was two million years ago"},{"time":521347,"text":"when we became humanoids"},{"time":522583,"text":"and developed these large foreheads."},{"time":524177,"text":"Other primates have a slanted brow."},{"time":526760,"text":"They don't have the frontal cortex."},{"time":528505,"text":"But the frontal cortex is not\nreally qualitatively different."},{"time":532190,"text":"It's a quantitative expansion of neocortex,"},{"time":534933,"text":"but that additional quantity of thinking"},{"time":537636,"text":"was the enabling factor for us to take"},{"time":539415,"text":"a qualitative leap and invent language"},{"time":542761,"text":"and art and science and technology"},{"time":544728,"text":"and TED conferences."},{"time":546182,"text":"No other species has done that."}]},{"cues":[{"time":548313,"text":"And so, over the next few decades,"},{"time":550388,"text":"we're going to do it again."},{"time":552148,"text":"We're going to again expand our neocortex,"},{"time":554422,"text":"only this time we won't be limited"},{"time":556178,"text":"by a fixed architecture of enclosure."},{"time":560458,"text":"It'll be expanded without limit."},{"time":563762,"text":"That additional quantity will again"},{"time":566005,"text":"be the enabling factor for another qualitative leap"},{"time":569010,"text":"in culture and technology."}]},{"cues":[{"time":570645,"text":"Thank you very much."}]},{"cues":[{"time":572699,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}